{
  "texts": [
    "Each time a new document is added to the database, the system indexes it for future comparisons with submitted assignments (Buckley & Cowap, 2013).",
    "However, Turnitin is not without flaws.",
    "Its algorithm may produce false positives, mistaking legitimate citations or shared texts for plagiarism.",
    "Additionally, there are privacy and copyright concerns regarding Turnitin's database.",
    "Student submissions might be permanently stored in the database, and unauthorized use could infringe on their privacy and intellectual property rights (Zaza & McKenzie, 2018)."
  ]
}